WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.656
All living things

00:00:01.656 --> 00:00:03.313
need food to

00:00:03.313 --> 00:00:04.969
grow. While animals

00:00:04.969 --> 00:00:06.626
find food, plants

00:00:06.626 --> 00:00:08.283
make their own

00:00:08.283 --> 00:00:09.939
using sunlight.

00:00:09.939 --> 00:00:11.434
Inside plant leaves,

00:00:11.434 --> 00:00:12.928
there is a

00:00:12.928 --> 00:00:14.422
green pigment called

00:00:14.422 --> 00:00:15.917
chlorophyll. It acts

00:00:15.917 --> 00:00:17.411
like a solar

00:00:17.411 --> 00:00:18.905
panel to capture

00:00:18.905 --> 00:00:20.399
light.

00:00:20.399 --> 00:00:22.076
Plants also absorb

00:00:22.076 --> 00:00:23.753
water from the

00:00:23.753 --> 00:00:25.429
soil through roots,

00:00:25.429 --> 00:00:27.106
and pull in

00:00:27.106 --> 00:00:28.783
carbon dioxide gas

00:00:28.783 --> 00:00:30.459
from the air.

00:00:30.459 --> 00:00:32.199
Sunlight splits water

00:00:32.199 --> 00:00:33.939
and gas into

00:00:33.939 --> 00:00:35.679
glucose sugar for

00:00:35.679 --> 00:00:37.420
food, and releases

00:00:37.420 --> 00:00:39.160
clean oxygen for

00:00:39.160 --> 00:00:40.900
us to breathe.

